# Anti-Patterns

- Do not add unnecessary layers such as repositories over EF Core unless there is a clear need.
- Avoid excessive abstraction and over-engineering.
- Do not place business logic inside Blazor components.
- Do not use global or static mutable state for app behavior.
- Do not call `StateHasChanged()` manually unless it is genuinely necessary.
- Do not optimize prematurely without a concrete performance problem.
